    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-18T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-18T06:00:00-05:00" n="1351"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1351">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/7–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1351<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1351fn1">The gist of this message was included in telegram
                        No. 65 of July 19 from <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName> to
                            <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> (file No. 800.00
                        Summaries/7–1945).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-18T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 18, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1548. British Chargé<note n="2" xml:id="d1351fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BRJ1">Reginald James Bowker</persName>.</note> has
                    been advised by <persName corresp="#p_CCC1">Castillo</persName> that <persName
                        corresp="#p_AT1">Alba</persName> was last week instructed to inform British
                    FonOff that Spanish Govt considers that Russia by refusing to associate itself
                    with statutory regime in Tangier forfeited its rights under act of Algeciras and
                    that present Soviet claim to participation is consequently without juridical
                    basis, for which reason Spain cannot consent to such participation. (My 1452
                    July 5 repeated London 433 Paris 366 Tangier 79<note n="3" xml:id="d1351fn3">
                        <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d688">Document No. 668, printed in vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>) <persName corresp="#p_CCC1">Castillo</persName> admitted
                    however Spain could in fact do nothing to prevent Russian participation but
                    stated that should USSR be admitted to Tangier only course open to Spain, in
                    view of large Spanish colony and extensive Spanish interests in that zone
                    (repeated to London <pb facs="1609" n="1411" xml:id="pg_1411"/> as 456 Paris as
                    398 Tangier as 82), would be to renounce statute<note n="4" xml:id="d1351fn4">i.
                        e., the regime established for Tangier by the convention signed at Paris,
                        December 18, 1923.</note> and revert to capitulatory regime.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
